t%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edesires%20for%20connection%3C%2Fa%3E%20clear%20and%20still%20don't%20feel%20cared%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20The%20gossipy%20friend%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gossipy%20friend%20speculates%20about%20other%20people%20when%20they're%20not%20in%20the%20room.%20It%20makes%20you%20not%20trust%20her%20with%20your%20own%20secrets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20mean-spirited%20as%20gossip%20can%20be%2C%20the%20motivation%20is%20often%20less%20nefarious%2C%20Jackson%20said.%20Your%20friend%20might%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-we-gossip-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrying%20to%20bond%20with%20you%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20her%20own%20insecurities%2C%20or%20just%20be%20bored%20with%20her%20own%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20suggested%20a%20few%20ways%20to%20gently%20redirect%20these%20conversations.%20If%20the%20dynamic%20makes%20it%20hard%20to%20enjoy%20your%20time%20together%2C%20it's%20worth%20reevaluating%20the%20friendship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20The%20love-obsessed%20friend%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20love-obsessed%20friend%20always%20has%20dating%20drama%20to%20fill%20you%20in%20on.%20This%20behavior%20is%20particularly%20grating%20if%20they%20disappear%20every%20time%20they're%20in%20a%20new%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJackson%20said%20this%20friend%20might%20be%20dealing%20with%20family%20or%20societal%20pressure%20to%20find%20a%20partner.%20And%20if%20they%20seem%20isolated%20in%20one%20particular%20relationship%2C%20it%20could%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Femotional-abuse%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esign%20of%20emotional%20abuse%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJackson%20said%20it's%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20leave%20if%20the%20friend%20consistently%20makes%20you%20feel%20like%20a%20social%20placeholder%20during%20their%20single%20seasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20The%20controlling%20friend%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20controlling%20friend%20has%20trouble%20taking%20%26quot%3Bno%26quot%3B%20for%20an%20answer%2C%20makes%20you%20feel%20guilty%20for%20disagreeing%20with%20them%2C%20and%20generally%20has%20issues%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-symptoms-you-are-struggling-with-emotional-dysregulation-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregulating%20their%20emotions%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20intense%20as%20this%20friend%20can%20be%2C%20Jackson%20said%20their%20behavior%20can%20stem%20from%20fear%20or%20anxiety.%20They%20might%20have%20less%20agency%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20their%20life%2C%20believing%20that%20your%20friendship%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20things%20they%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJackson%20said%20it's%20worth%20trying%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-right-way-to-set-boundaries-with-people-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egently%20state%20your%20boundaries.%3C%2Fa%3E%20If%20they%20don't%20make%20an%20effort%20to%20change%2C%20it's%20unhealthy%20to%20keep%20walking%20on%20eggshells.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20The%20jealous%20friend%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubtle-signs-your-friend-is-jealous-of-you-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejealous%20friend%3C%2Fa%3E%20responds%20to%20your%20good%20news%20with%20sarcasm%2C%20dismissal%2C%20or%20criticism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJackson%20said%20that%20envy%20can%20come%20from%20a%20friend's%20fixed%20mindset%2C%20believing%20that%20you%20getting%20your%20dream%20job%20reduces%20her%20opportunity%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20that%20means%20you%20have%20to%20tolerate%20rude%20behavior%20though.%20In%20the%20book%2C%20Jackson%20suggests%20a%20few%20ways%20to%20delicately%20approach%20this%20issue.%20If%20nothing%20changes%2C%20you%20can%20distance%20yourself%20for%20the%20time%20being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20The%20newly%20changed%20friend%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20newly%20changed%20friend%20suddenly%20has%20new%20interests%2C%20friends%2C%20clothes%2C%20or%20anything%20else%20that%20makes%20you%20wonder%20if%20you're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-you-outgrowing-done-friendship-move-past-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutgrowing%20each%20other%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJackson%20said%20that%20these%20shifts%20might%20come%20from%20a%20friend%20experimenting%20with%20her%20identity%2C%20which%20is%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20encourages%20trying%20to%20find%20what%20you%20both%20still%20have%20in%20common%2C%20with%20one%20caveat%3A%20you%20should%20still%20feel%20safe%20around%20them.%20If%20your%20friend%20adopts%20world%20views%20that%20directly%20conflict%20with%20your%20identity%20or%20safety%2C%20Jackson%20said%20that's%20ample%20reason%20to%20quit%20the%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20The%20clingy%20friend%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJackson%20defines%20a%20clingy%20friend%20as%20needing%20frequent%20contact%20and%20reassurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20she%20said%2C%20this%20can%20just%20boil%20down%20to%20a%20difference%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-3-different-attachment-styles-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattachment%20styles%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20if%20you're%20avoidant%2C%20a%20friend's%20texts%20might%20come%20off%20more%20anxious%20than%20they%20actually%20are.%20You%20might%20also%20have%20different%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftypes-of-communication-styles-improve-friendship-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommunication%20styles%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20expectations%20of%20support%20in%20a%20friendship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20deeper%20level%2C%20Jackson%20said%20you%20might%20unknowingly