ower-and-industrial-solutions-q4-results-profit-dips-10-to-rs-234-cr-124050600514_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Aditi%20exudes%20major%20ethnic%20fashion%20inspiration%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714991400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109884158%2Cimgsize-88520.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Faditi-rao-hydari-exudes-major-ethnic-fashion-inspiration-in-a-vibrant-outfit%2Fphotostory%2F109884158.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F109884158.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAditi%20Rao%20Hydari%20radiates%20regal%20vibes%20in%20a%20violet%20outfit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Faditi-rao-hydari-exudes-major-ethnic-fashion-inspiration-in-a-vibrant-outfit%2Fphotostory%2F109884158.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20most%20hated%20workplace%20software%20on%20the%20planet%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hands%20aggressively%20pointing%20at%20a%20Workday%20App%2C%20with%20exclamation%20marks%20emanating%20from%20the%20app%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661986fd3f923f7dab077eac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BGetting%20someone%20onboarded%20using%20Workday%20is%20like%20trying%20to%20get%20water%20from%20your%20sink%20to%20your%20stove%20using%20a%20colander%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20director%20at%20a%20startup.%3Cp%3EWorkday%3B%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20hunted%20for%20a%20job%20in%20the%20past%20decade%20or%20so%2C%20you've%20likely%20encountered%20the%20following%20obstacle%20course.%20Applying%20to%20a%20desired%20role%20online%2C%20you're%20greeted%20with%20a%20login%20prompt.%20The%20employer%20is%20asking%20you%20to%20create%20a%20profile%20to%20apply%3F%20Annoying%2C%20but%20you%20go%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20given%20a%20long%20form%20to%20fill%20out%20with%20the%20information%20that's%20already%20on%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%20In%20a%20world%20where%20we%20can%20all%20attach%20PDFs%2C%20this%20seems%20unnecessary%2C%20but%20%E2%80%94%20ah%2C%20phew%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20form%20promises%20to%20autofill%20the%20entries%20if%20you%20simply%20drag%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20over%2C%20and%20%E2%80%94%20oh%2C%20crap.%20It%20loads%20all%20wrong.%20Your%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ework%20experience%20is%20scattered%20across%20the%20lines%20that%20want%20your%20name%20and%20address.%20Your%20address%2C%20truncated%2C%20is%20where%20your%20college%20degree%20should%20be.%20It's%20a%20mess.%20You%20find%20it's%20easier%20to%20delete%20it%20all%20and%20manually%20type%20in%20each%20entry.%20How%20obnoxious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%2C%20applying%20to%20a%20different%20job%20at%20a%20different%20company%2C%20you%20click%20through%20and%20see%20the%20same%20form.%20You%20recognize%20the%20logo%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20page%3A%20a%20blue%20W%20with%20a%20yellow%20arch%20cresting%20above%20it.%20Is%20the%20arch%20a%20%E2%80%A6%20frown%3F%20Geez.%20But%20you'd%20set%20up%20a%20user%20ID%20to%20apply%20to%20the%20previous%20job%2C%20so%20this%20should%20be%20%E2%80%94%20huh%3F%20It%20wants%20an%20entirely%20new%20ID.%20New%20company%2C%20new%20profile%2C%20new%20form.%20Oof.%20Surely%20it%20saved%20your%20application%20entries%20from%20the%20other%20job%2C%20right%3F%20Nope.%20Does%20the%20autofill%20work%20this%20time%3F%20Of%20course%20it%20doesn't.%20Another%20half-hour%20of%20formatting%20and%20you're%20done%20with%20the%20application%20%E2%80%94%20and%20so%20done%20with%20whichever%20confounding%20organization%20decided%20to%20execute%20these%20tasks%20this%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20you%20find%20another%20job%20opening%20and%20%E2%80%94%20no.%20No!%20So%20the%20logo%20%3Cem%3Eis%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20frown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20devising%20this%20torture%20that%20is%20the%20modern%20job%20application%20is%20called%20Workday.%20Since%202006%2C%20Workday%2C%20which%20provides%20software%20for%20payroll%2C%20talent%20management%2C%20and%20expense%20processing%2C%20has%20been%20making%20a%20mint%20creating%20misery%20where%20painless%20processes%20could%20be.%20More%20than%20half%20of%20the%20Fortune%20500%20companies%20use%20Workday%20to%20pay%2C%20hire%2C%20onboard%2C%20and%20administer%20benefits%20to%20their%20employees.%20Clients%20range%20from%20Netflix%20to%20Goodwill%2C%20Spotify%20to%20The%20Washington%20Post%2C%20Chick-fil-A%20to%20Ohio%20State%20University.%20Trillions%20of%20dollars%20in%20revenue%20and%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20employees%20are%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20Workday's%20back-end%20people-management%20software.%20The%20company%20is%20worth%20some%20%2470%20billion%2C%20a%20market%20cap%20greater%20than%20that%20of%20FedEx%2C%20Nintendo%2C%20or%20Honda.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFew%20seem%20happy%20about%20this.%20LinkedIn%2C%20Reddit%2C%20and%20Blind%20abound%20with%20enraged%20job%20applicants%20and%20employees%20sharing%20tales%20of%20how%20difficult%20it%20is%20to%20book%20paid%20leave%2C%20how%20Kafkaesque%20it%20is%20to%20file%20an%20expense%2C%20how%20nerve-racking%20it%20is%20to%20close%20out%20a%20project.%20%26quot%3BI%20simply%20hate%20Workday.%20Fuck%20them%20and%20those%20who%20insist%20on%20using%20it%20for%20recruitment%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20Reddit%20user%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20is%20non-intuitive%2C%20so%20even%20the%20simplest%20tasks%20leave%20me%20scratching%20my%20head%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20another.%20%26quot%3BKeeping%20notes%20on%20index%20cards%20would%20be%20more%20effective.%26quot%3B%20Every%20HR%20professional%20and%20hiring%20manager%20I%20spoke%20with%20%E2%80%94%20whose%20lives%20are%20supposedly%20made%20easier%20by%20Workday%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0described%20Workday%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20cosmic%20exasperation.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20constantly%20being%20botsmacked%20by%20bureaucracy%20incarnate%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20copy%20director%20at%20an%20AI%20startup%20in%20San%20Francisco%20who%20had%20the%20misfortune%20of%20having%20to%20hire%20contractors%20through%20Workday.%20He%20went%20on%3A%20%26quot%3BGetting%20someone%20onboarded%20using%20Workday%20is%20like%20trying%20to%20get%20water%20from%20your%20sink%20to%20your%20stove%20using%20a%20colander.%26quot%3B%20The%20X%20account%20Work%20Day%20Failing%20tracks%20memes%20and%20news%20articles%20describing%20workers%20and%20companies%20suffering%20within%20various%20circles%20of%20Workday%20hell%2C%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ends-deal-workday-hr-software-partnership-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon's%20failed%20migration%20to%20Workday%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%20(after%20which%20Workday's%20stock%20dropped%20by%207%25)%20to%20an%20ongoing%20class-action%20lawsuit%20that%20alleges%20Workday%20uses%20AI%20to%20discriminate%20against%20candidates%20based%20on%20race%2C%20age%2C%20and%20disability.%20(%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20this%20lawsuit%20is%20without%20merit%20and%20deny%20the%20allegations%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20Workday%20spokesperson.%20%26quot%3BWorkday%20does%20not%20have%20oversight%20or%20control%20of%20our%20customers'%20job%20application%20processes.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20candidates%20hate%20Workday%2C%20if%20employees%20hate%20Workday%2C%20if%20HR%20people%20and%20managers%20processing%20and%20assessing%20those%20candidates%20and%20employees%20through%20Workday%20hate%20Workday%20%E2%80%94%20if%20Workday%20is%20the%20most%20annoying%20part%20of%20so%20many%20workers'%20workdays%20%E2%80%94%20how%20is%20Workday%20everywhere%3F%20How%20did%20a%20software%20provider%20so%20widely%20loathed%20become%20a%20mainstay%20of%20the%20modern%20workplace%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%2C%20to%20use%20a%20term%20that%20any%20client%20of%20Workday%20could%20surely%20use%2C%20is%20POSIWID.%20This%20is%20a%20saying%20in%20systems%20thinking%3A%20The%20purpose%20of%20a%20system%20is%20what%20it%20does%20(POSIWID)%2C%20not%20what%20it%20fails%20to%20do.%20And%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20what%20Workday%20%E2%80%94%20and%20its%20many%20despised%20competitors%20%E2%80%94%20does%20for%20organizations%20is%20far%20more%20important%20than%20the%20anguish%20it%20causes%20everyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20160%20million%20Americans%20with%20jobs%2C%20about%20130%20million%20of%20us%20aren't%20self-employed%20or%20don't%20own%20a%20business%20and%20so%20receive%20wages%20and%20health-insurance%20plans%20through%20our%20employers.%20Serving%20these%20130%20million%20people%20are%20roughly%201%20million%20human-resources%20professionals.%20That's%20an%20impossible%20shit%20ton%20of%20hirings%2C%20firings%2C%20withheld%20taxes%2C%20expenses%2C%20paid%20leaves%2C%20orientation%20trainings%2C%20and%20professional-growth%20reviews%20to%20keep%20track%20of.%20It's%20a%20world%20of%20paperwork%20that%20software%20is%20eager%20to%20eat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20late%2020th%20century%2C%20companies%20moved%20more%20and%20more%20of%20that%20recordkeeping%20from%20filing%20cabinets%20to%20mainframe%20computers%20and%20then%20to%20servers.%20In%201988%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oracle.com%2Fapplications%2Fpeoplesoft%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeopleSoft%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20backed%20by%20IBM%2C%20built%20the%20first%20fully%20fledged%20Human%20Resources%20Information%20System.%20In%202004%2C%20Oracle%20acquired%20PeopleSoft%20for%20%2410.3%20billion.%20One%20of%20its%20founders%2C%20David%20Duffield%2C%20then%20started%20a%20new%20company%20that%20upgraded%20PeopleSoft's%20model%20to%20near%20limitless%20cloud-based%20storage%20%E2%80%94%20giving%20birth%20to%20Workday%2C%20the%20intractable%20nepo%20baby%20of%20HR%20software.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20its%20predecessors%2C%20Workday%20stores%20our%20applications%20and%20profiles%20as%20objects%20that%20relate%20to%20each%20other%2C%20linked%20with%20metadata.%20How%20this%20works%20is%20less%20important%20than%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20means%20Workday%20could%20conceivably%20build%20its%20%3Cem%3Eown%3C%2Fem%3E%20encrypted%20database%20of%20our%20information%2C%20across%20our%20different%20jobs%20and%20applications.%20When%20you%20leave%20Spotify%20to%20go%20work%20at%20Netflix%2C%20your%20profile%20could%20follow%20you%2C%20allowing%20you%20to%20more%20easily%20apply%20to%20the%20job.%20The%20multiplying%20powers%20of%20tech%20could%20scale%20to%20free%20us%20of%20our%20busy%20work%2C%20as%20promised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Workday's%20servers%20belong%20with%20its%20clients%2C%20and%20so%20it%20can't%20(or%20won't)%20do%20this.%20Does%20Workday%20want%20to%20carry%20the%20liability%20of%20a%20data%20breach%20that%20could%20damage%20half%20of%20the%20Fortune%20500%3F%20Probably%20not.%20A%20Workday%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20Workday's%20clients%20%26quot%3Bconfigure%20the%20application%20process%20for%20each%20job%20to%20fit%20their%20unique%20hiring%20processes%20and%20needs.%26quot%3B%20She%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BOur%20customers%20retain%20control%20over%20their%20own%20data.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20raises%20another%20point%3A%20Workday%20is%20indifferent%20to%20our%20suffering%20in%20a%20job%20hunt%2C%20because%20we%20aren't%20Workday's%20clients%2C%20companies%20are.%20And%20these%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20from%20AT%26amp%3BT%20to%20Bank%20of%20America%20to%20Teladoc%20%E2%80%94%20have%20little%20incentive%20to%20care%20about%20your%20application%20experience%2C%20because%20if%20you%20didn't%20get%20the%20job%2C%20you're%20not%20their%20responsibility.%20For%20a%20company%20hiring%20and%20onboarding%20on%20a%20global%20scale%2C%20it%20is%20simply%20easier%20to%20screen%20fewer%20candidates%20if%20the%20result%20is%20still%20a%20single%20hire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20because%20Workday%20is%20a%20jack%20of%20all%20trades%20program%20(recruiting%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20finance%20%3Cem%3Eand%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecompany-wide%20planning%20etc.%20etc.)%2C%20the%20supposed%20convenience%20of%20an%20all-in-one%20platform%20often%20come%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20creating%20frustrating%20%3Cem%3Enew%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theregister.com%2F2021%2F01%2F04%2Fworkday_problems_persist_at_mcgill%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproblems%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20clients.%20At%20one%20major%20university%20last%20year%2C%20migrating%20its%20IT%20%E2%80%94%20including%2011%2C000%20outstanding%20invoices%20%E2%80%94%20to%20Workday%20became%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.geekwire.com%2F2023%2Funiv-of-washington-struggles-with-new-finance-system-highlighting-it-migration-difficulties%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efull-blown%20fiasco%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20search%20on%20a%20job%20board%20can%20return%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fjobs%2Fsearch%2F%3FcurrentJobId%3D3848375782%26keywords%3Dworkday%2520consultant%26origin%3DSWITCH_SEARCH_VERTICAL%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehundreds%20of%20listings%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20in-house%20Workday%20consultants%3A%C2%A0IT%20and%20engineering%20professionals%20hired%20to%20fix%20the%20software%20promising%20to%20fix%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20recruiters%2C%20Workday%20also%20lacks%20basic%20user-interface%20flexibility.%20When%20you%20promise%20ease-of-use%20and%20simplicity%2C%20you%20must%20deliver%20on%20the%20most%20basic%20user%20interactions.%20And%20yet%3A%20Sometimes%20searching%20for%20a%20candidate%2C%20or%20locating%20a%20candidate's%20status%20feels%20impossible.%20This%20happens%20outside%20of%20recruiting%2C%20too%2C%20where%20locating%20or%20attaching%20a%20boss's%20email%20to%20approve%20an%20expense%20sheet%20is%20complicated%20by%20the%20process%2C%20not%20streamlined.%20Bureaucratic%20hell%20is%20always%20about%20one%20person's%20ease%20coming%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20someone%20else's%20frustration%2C%20time%20wasted%2C%20and%20busy%20work.%20Workday%20makes%20no%20exceptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkday%20touts%20its%20ability%20to%20track%20employee%20performance%20by%20collecting%20data%20and%20marking%20results%2C%20but%20it%20is%20employees%20who%20must%20spend%20time%20inputting%20this%20data.%20A%20creative%20director%20at%20a%20Fortune%20500%20company%20told%20me%20how%20in%20less%20than%20two%20years%20his%20company%20went%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20annual%20reviews%20to%20twice-annual%20reviews%20to%20quarterly%20reviews%20to%20quarterly%20reviews%20plus%20separate%20twice-annual%20reviews.%26quot%3B%20At%20each%20interval%20higher-ups%20pressed%20HR%20for%20more%20data%2C%20because%20they%20wanted%20what%20they'd%20paid%20for%20with%20Workday%3A%20more%20work%20product.%20With%20a%20press%20of%20a%20button%2C%20HR%20could%20provide%20that%2C%20but%20the%20entire%20company%20suffered%20thousands%20more%20hours%20of%20busy%20work.%20Automation%20made%20it%20%3Cem%3Etoo%3C%2Fem%3E%20easy%20to%20do%20too%20much.%20(Workday's%20%26quot%3Bcustomers%20choose%20the%20frequency%20at%20which%20they%20conduct%20reviews%2C%20not%20Workday%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20spokesperson.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20Workday%20has%20innumerable%20competitors%2C%20their%20names%20as%20ridiculous%20as%20their%20sheer%20volume.%20We%20have%20Dayforce%2C%20Zenefits%2C%20and%20Sage.%20We%20must%20not%20confuse%20Paycom%20with%20Paycor%2C%20or%20Kudos%20with%20Kudoboard.%20How%20dare%20you%20mistake%20Namely%20or%20Cornerstone%20for%20Rippling.%20Beyond%20standard%20HR%20Information%20Systems%2C%20legions%20of%20niche%20operators%20offer%20add-ons%20to%20boost%20employee%20engagement%2C%20from%20Bonusly%20(really)%20to%20BucketList%20(sad%20but%20true)%2C%20to%20Motivosity%20(yes).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAre%20any%20of%20these%20better%2C%20or%20are%20they%20all%20maligned%3F%20As%20easily%20as%20you%20can%20find%20a%20founder%20who%20hates%20UKG%20Pro%20but%20loves%20Rippling%20you%20can%20find%20a%20similar%20rant%20from%20another%20founder%20ripping%20Rippling%20a%20new%20one.%20HR%20and%20payroll%20and%20recruiting%20are%20unenviable%20tasks%2C%20and%20not%20easy%20even%20before%20scale.%20At%20the%20scale%20of%20a%20large%20company%2C%20this%20is%20simply%20too%20much%20work%20to%20expect%20a%20few%20people%20to%20do%20and%20far%20too%20user-specific%20to%20expect%20automation%20to%20handle%20well.%20It's%20why%20Workday%20can%20be%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20worst%3C%2Fem%3E%20while%20still%20allowing%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Finvinceabella%2Fstatus%2F718399996517838848%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPaychex%20is%20the%20worst%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FCodywaynegroves%2Fstatus%2F1557835464635256832%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPaycom%20is%20the%20worst%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAuthenikk2%2Fstatus%2F1369631631527587845%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPaycor%20is%20the%20worst%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fchris_fedak%2Fstatus%2F469870651952480256%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDayforce%20is%20the%20worst%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BHR%20software%20sucking%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20big%20tent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20writer%20and%20tech%20critic%20Cory%20Doctorow%20coined%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Benshittification%26quot%3B%20to%20describe%20how%20internet%20platforms%20inevitably%20decay.%20First%2C%20platforms%20are%20good%20to%20their%20users%2C%20creating%20value%20(Facebook%2C%20where%20people%20can%20connect%20and%20share%20their%20lives%20with%20one%20another).%20Then%20they%20abuse%20their%20users%20to%20make%20money%20for%20their%20%3Cem%3Eactual%3C%2Fem%3E%20customers%2C%20advertisers%20or%20businesses%20(Facebook%2C%20where%20we%20sell%20your%20data%20to%20inundate%20you%20with%20ads).%20Then%20they%20abuse%20those%20business%20customers%20to%20try%20to%20recoup%20revenue%20for%20themselves%20(Facebook%2C%20pivoting%20to%20video).%20Then%20platforms%20die.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkday%20finds%20itself%20between%20enshittification%20steps%20two%20and%20three.%20The%20platform%20once%20made%20things%20faster%2C%20simpler%20for%20workers.%20But%20today%20it%20abuses%20workers%20by%20cutting%20corners%20on%20job-application%20and%20reimbursement%20procedures.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20it%20provides%20the%20value%20of%20a%20one-stop%20HR%20shop%20to%20its%20paying%20customers.%20It%20seems%20it's%20only%20a%20matter%20of%20time%20before%20Workday%20and%20its%20competitors%20try%20to%20split%20the%20difference%20and%20cut%20those%20same%20corners%20with%20the%20accounts%20that%20pay%20their%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkday%20reveals%20what's%20important%20to%20the%20people%20who%20run%20Fortune%20500%20companies%3A%20easily%20and%20conveniently%20distributing%20busy%20work%20across%20large%20workforces.%20This%20is%20done%20with%20the%20arbitrary%20and%20perfunctory%20performance%20of%20work%20tasks%20(like%20excessive%20reviews)%20and%20with%20the%20throttling%20of%20momentum%20by%20making%20finance%20and%20HR%20tasks%20difficult.%20If%20your%20expenses%20and%20reimbursements%20are%20difficult%20to%20file%2C%20that's%20OK%2C%20because%20the%20people%20above%20you%20don't%20actually%20care%20if%20you%20get%20reimbursed.%20If%20it%20takes%20applicants%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fjob-hunting-sucks-programmer-filled-out-250-applications%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E128%25%20longer%20to%20apply%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20people%20who%20implemented%20Workday%20don't%20really%20care.%20Throttling%20applicants%20is%20perhaps%20not%20intentional%2C%20but%20it's%20%3Cem%3Egood%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECustomer%20service%20is%20Workday's%20goal.%20It's%20just%20that%20the%20customer%20isn't%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20once%20worked%20at%20a%20cocktail%20lounge%20with%20a%20creaky%20board%20behind%20the%20bar%2C%20and%20the%20owner%20refused%20to%C2%A0fix%20it.%20We%20all%20complained%20nonstop%20about%20the%20board%2C%20but%20never%20about%20him.%20He'd%20seemed%20to%20realize%20the%20same%20net%20benefit%20that%20Workday%20and%20all%20of%20its%20love-to-hate-them%20competitors%20provide%20us%20in%20the%20modern%20workplace%3A%20Nothing%20brings%20people%20together%20like%20a%20common%20enemy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fmatt-alston%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMatt%20Alston%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E's%20writing%20has%20appeared%20in%20Wired%2C%20Rolling%20Stone%2C%20Playboy%2C%20and%20Believer.%20He%20trained%20as%20a%20civil%20engineer%2C%20and%20now%20works%20as%20a%20copywriter%20in%20tech.%20He%20lives%20in%20Maine%20with%20his%C2%A0wife%20and%20daughter.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feveryone-hates-workday-human-resources-customer-service-software-fortune-500-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714991281000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661986fd1caec1275a6fbab2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feveryone-hates-workday-human-resources-customer-service-software-fortune-500-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20creates%20mountains%20of%20busywork%20for%20everyone.%20So%20why%20do%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20companies%20in%20the%20Fortune%20500%20use%20it%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Matt%20Alston)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22can