0This%20method%20is%20very%20effective%20in%20homes%20in%20the%20northern%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20where%20the%20humidity%20is%20relatively%20low%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ETrees%20and%20shade%20keep%20your%20home%20happy%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrees%20have%20been%20the%20best%20friends%20of%20humans%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20time.%20From%20giving%20us%20food%20to%20shelter%20under%20its%20shade%2C%20trees%20are%20something%20that%20the%20architects%20advise%20to%20have%20around%20the%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20cannot%20emphasise%20enough%20the%20need%20and%20importance%20of%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F348074%2Fsustainable-home-wayanad-kerala-george-ramapuram-earthitects-hillside-jungle-home-nature%2F%23google_vignette%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20trees%20around%20your%20home%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20bring%20in%20shade%2C%20and%20wind%20and%20moderate%20the%20temperature%20around%20them.%20Plant%20as%20many%20trees%20as%20you%20can%20around%20your%20home%20and%20try%20to%20incorporate%20the%20existing%20ones%20in%20the%20design.%20Trust%20me%2C%20they%20are%20going%20to%20be%20a%20lifesaver%20in%20the%20heat%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20George%20Ramapuran%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20sustainable%20design%20firm%2C%20Eartitects.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20built%20numerous%20estates%20around%20the%20theme%20of%20sustainability%20and%20nature%20conservation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgreeing%20with%20George%2C%20Shipra%20also%20emphasises%20the%20importance%20of%20greenery%20to%20keep%20the%20heat%20at%20bay.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20constructing%20the%20home%2C%20you%20can%20always%20look%20at%20the%20region-specific%20trees%20and%20plant%20them%20in%20the%20areas%20where%20your%20home%20will%20have%20verandas%20and%20windows.%20This%20will%20ensure%20shade%20in%20those%20areas%20and%20also%20will%20help%20in%20better%20wind%20circulation%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20840px)%20100vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fveedu-1-1-1-1694786484.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Architects%20suggest%20planting%20trees%20around%20the%20house%20to%20increase%20shade%20and%20reduce%20temperatures.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fveedu-1-1-1-1694786484.jpg%20840w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fveedu-1-1-1-1694786484-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fveedu-1-1-1-1694786484-500x261.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fveedu-1-1-1-1694786484-768x401.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fveedu-1-1-1-1694786484-150x78.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-330098%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22439%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EArchitects%20suggest%20planting%20trees%20around%20the%20house%20to%20increase%20shade%20and%20reduce%20temperatures.%20Picture%20credit%3A%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EDirection%20of%20the%20wind%20and%20sun%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20the%20direction%20of%20the%20wind%20and%20sun%20is%20very%20important%20while%20constructing%20your%20home.%20%E2%80%9CPlanning%20is%20crucial%20when%20constructing%20a%20house.%20The%20western%20sun%20can%20be%20harsh%2C%20while%20the%20southern%20exposure%20brings%20in%20heat.%20It%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20build%20verandas%20on%20these%20sides%20of%20the%20house%20to%20help%20filter%20the%20sunlight%20and%20reduce%20the%20heat%20entering%20the%20home%2C%E2%80%9D%20advises%20George.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20also%20include%20things%20like%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Ejaalis%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(lattice)%20and%20smaller%20openings%2C%20other%20than%20windows%20and%20verandahs%2C%20advises%20Shirpa.%20Samira%2C%20too%2C%20emphasises%20the%20importance%20of%20%3Cem%3Ejaali%20%3C%2Fem%3Estructures%20to%20increase%20more%20wind%20and%20natural%20light%20inside%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShipra%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20roof%2C%20you%20could%20consider%20making%20it%20slanting%20instead.%20While%20modern%20designs%20do%20not%20support%20it%2C%20such%20roofs%20are%20really%20good%20for%20homes.%20They%20bring%20in%20more%20shade%20in%20the%20house%2C%20they%20look%20authentic%20and%20the%20sun%20is%20never%20hitting%20the%20entire%20roof%20at%20one%20time.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ENatural%20materials%20make%20a%20cooler%20home%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20materials%2C%20the%20three%20architects%20agree%20that%20using%20natural%20materials%20can%20bring%20down%20the%20temperatures%20significantly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CStudy%20the%20area%20well%20before%20you%20start%20constructing%20your%20home.%20By%20knowing%20the%20area%20well%2C%20you%20can%20find%20natural%20and%20traditional%20materials%20to%20build%20your%20home.%20Mangalore%20tiles%20are%20something%20that%20I%20recommend%20to%20all%20my%20clients.%20These%20tiles%20are%20very%20durable%20and%20breathable.%20A%20Mangalore%20tiled%20roof%20is%20not%20concrete%20and%20has%20space%20for%20cross%20ventilation%20letting%20the%20house%20breathe%2C%E2%80%9D%20George%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20materials%20such%20as%20wood%20and%20stones%20for%20construction%20instead%20of%20cement%20can%20also%20do%20wonders%20for%20the%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAgain%2C%20I%20would%20emphasise%20the%20use%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F348313%2Falwar-zero-cement-sustainable-home-rainwater-harvesting-neem-jaggery-built-by-shipra-singhania%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraditional%20materials%20such%20as%20mud%2C%20straw%20and%20lime%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20make%20homes.%20Mud%20is%20a%20natural%20coolant%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20turning%20towards%20mud%20homes.%20Additionally%2C%20using%20lime%20on%20the%20floor%20or%20the%20walls%20can%20also%20help%20you%20bring%20down%20the%20temperature%20of%20the%20house%20significantly%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Shipra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFor%20existing%20apartments%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20a%20home%20that%20is%20already%20constructed%20and%20has%20no%20scope%20for%20reconstruction%2C%20there%20are%20some%20%3Cem%3Ejugaads%20(quick%20fixes)%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20these%20architects%20have%20suggested.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2Fmud-house--1702472206.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Using%20materials%20such%20as%20mud%2C%20straw%20and%20lime%20can%20keep%20the%20house%20naturally%20cool.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2Fmud-house--1702472206.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2Fmud-house--1702472206-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2Fmud-house--1702472206-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2Fmud-house--1702472206-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2Fmud-house--1702472206-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-335983%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EUsing%20materials%20such%20as%20mud%2C%20straw%20and%20lime%20can%20keep%20the%20house%20naturally%20cool.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20Consider%20building%20a%20small%20terrace%20garden%20for%20increased%20greenery%20and%20shade%20in%20the%20home%2C%20suggests%20George.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20You%20can%20also%20consider%20painting%20your%20roof%20white%20so%20that%20it%20reflects%20some%20of%20the%20heat.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20quite%20effective%20and%20I%20have%20done%20it%20in%20my%20own%20home%20too%2C%E2%80%9D%20George%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20Sherpa%20advises%20using%20%3Cem%3EKhus%20(%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20native%20Indian%20grass%20which%20has%20traditionally%20been%20used%20as%20a%20coolant%20in%20Indian%20households)%20or%20any%20dried%20grass%20sheet%2C%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20typically%20used%20in%20coolers%20on%20your%20windows.%20If%20you%20water%20them%2C%20the%20wind%20that%20comes%20through%20them%20will%20be%20cooler.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20You%20can%20also%20use%20terracotta%20coolers%20that%20many%20innovators%20have%20made%20to%20keep%20the%20home%20cool%20as%20they%20are%20more%20sustainable%20in%20nature.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20One%20important%20principle%20that%20is%20often%20ignored%20in%20practice%20is%20that%20there%20is%20no%20%E2%80%98one-size-fits-all%E2%80%99%20solution.%20%E2%80%9CMost%20regions%20have%20traditional%20techniques%20for%20passive%20cooling%20that%20are%20often%20overlooked%20by%20modern%20architecture%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ayesha%20Jhunjhunwala%2C%20an%20architect%20and%20director%20of%20Coonoor%20Estates.%20You%20can%20consider%20trying%20out%20traditional%20methods%20to%20cool%20your%20home%2C%20she%20advises.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20in%20hot%2C%20dry%20climates%20such%20as%20Rajasthan%2C%20a%20layer%20of%20inverted%20mud%20pots%20on%20the%20roof%20of%20a%20structure%20can%20significantly%20reduce%20the%20temperature%20of%20the%20building.%20This%20effect%20is%20strongest%20when%20the%20pots%20are%20painted%20white%20to%20increase%20the%20amount%20of%20sunlight%20reflected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714487577000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F71e1f2ce8e654135b509da9fba6c6619_311592766_142412935197808_3738696823372802622_n-1680175563.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D348728%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20soaring%20temperatures%20and%20warnings%20of%20heatwaves%20in%20several%20Indian%20cities%2C%20architects%20share%20how%20to%20build%20homes%20that%20stay%20naturally%20cool%20and%20don't%20require%20air%20conditioning%20at%20all%20times.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Tina%20Freese%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F348728%2Fheatwaves-imd-warning-architect-tips-keep-home-naturally-cool-air-conditioning-summer-india%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Order%20Organic%20Mangoes%20From%20Farms%20Across%20India%20Using%208%20Online%20Platforms%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDo%20you%20remember%20rushing%20home%20from%20school%20to%20savour%20a%20bowl%20filled%20with%20fleshy%2C%20yellow%20squares%20of%20delight%3F%20I%20do.%20Summer%20afternoons%20often%20meant%20eyeing%20the%20neighbour%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Ekairi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(raw%20mango)%20trees%2C%20elated%20when%20the%20green%20beauties%20would%20fall%20to%20the%20ground%20and%20be%20almost%20immediately%20scooped%20into%20our%20baskets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20summer%20progresses%2C%20no%20Indian%20is%20a%20stranger%20to%20the%20long%20wait%20that%20ensues%20for%20the%20yellowish-green%20hues%20to%20transform%20into%20its%20ripe%20golden-orange%20form.%20And%20no%20one%20questions%20the%20long%20queues%20outside%20popular%20Gujarati%20joints%20whose%20%3Cem%3Eaamras%20puri%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20dish%20of%20sweet%20mango%20pulp%20served%20with%20deep-fried%20flatbread)%20is%20%E2%80%9Cto%20die%20for%E2%80%9D%2C%20according%20to%20the%20regulars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20juicy%20fact%20that%20summers%20in%20India%20are%20incomplete%20without%20mango%20dominating%20our%20homes%20and%20palates.%20This%20comes%20as%20no%20surprise.%20Indians%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F57267%2Fmango-national-fruit-of-india-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecultivating%20mangoes%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20thousands%20of%20years%2C%20and%20till%20today%2C%20the%20love%20for%20the%20fruit%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20waned%20even%20one%20bit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Alphonso%20continues%20to%20hold%20its%20status%20as%20a%20cult%20favourite%20for%20its%20vibrant%20sweetness%20and%20distinct%20flavour%2C%20there%20are%20hundreds%2C%20if%20not%20thousands%20of%20varieties%20that%20dot%20the%20landscape%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20mango%20cultivation.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20lesser-known%20varieties%20make%20an%20appearance%20in%20chutneys%2C%20pickles%20and%20the%20like%2C%20lending%20them%20their%20citrusy%20flavour.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20if%20you%20haven%E2%80%99t%20got%20your%20stock%20of%20mangoes%20yet%2C%20here%E2%80%99s%20a%20suggestion%3A%20why%20not%20get%20them%20delivered%20to%20you%20straight%20from%20a%20farm%3F%20We%E2%80%99ve%20put%20together%20a%20list%20of%20people%2C%20startups%20and%20local%20platforms%20that%20are%20bringing%20the%20sweetness%20of%20the%20mango%20from%20the%20tree%20to%20your%20plate.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E1.%20Athalya%20Vandhu%20Ambewale%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCQoWEyej